  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "\r\ncontract-schema should respect Solidity's breaking [ABI changes](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/releases/tag/v0.6.0). Discussing with @gnidan `contract-schema` could use the solidity compiler version to populate the correct values in the `transform` and `normalize` would handle forward compatibility. This would be a breaking change to @truffle/contract-schema.\r\n\r\n## Breaking changes from Solidity release\r\n  - ABI: Remove the deprecated constant and payable fields.\r\n  - ABI: [The type field is now required and no longer specified to default to function](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/64b54ad493ab80d0cb377b5453c0dbb9c72b04e2/packages/contract-schema/spec/abi.spec.json#L45-L69).\r\n  - [Sample artifact that fails](https://ipfs.infura.io/ipfs/QmWk7BFpoWPeZBBw5QuafHVwdWVDSGNUTMBQMLWUuh6qrN/) validation.\r\n\r\nThanks @xMNG for bring this to our attention.\r\n[edit] bring notice to the `ABI type field` and add link to a reported failing contract",
